genresAdvancedInfo.name: medieval
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A music genre that originated in Europe during the Middle Ages, from the 5th to the 15th century. Medieval music is characterized by its use of monophonic melodies, often sung in Latin, and accompanied by simple instrumental accompaniment. The music is often religious in nature, with many pieces composed for use in church services. Medieval music is known for its haunting melodies and rich harmonies, and has influenced many modern music genres.
